    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Collection sites of Gracixalus lumarius sp. nov. (star = type locality)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4910722/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4910734>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. (A) High elevation bamboo forest at type locality of Gracixalus lumarius sp. nov. and (B) phyptotelm in which holotype of G. lumarius sp. nov. (AMS R 176202) and eggs (AMS R 176213) were collected." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4910734/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4910728>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Palmar surfaces of left hand (A) and plantar surface of left foot (B) of the male holotype of Gracixalus lumarius sp. nov. (AMS R 176202). Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4910728/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4910730>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Dorsal surfaces of preserved Gracixalus lumarius sp. nov. specimens (A) male holotype AMS R 176202, (B) male paratype AMS R 173889, (C) male paratype AMS R 173890, (D) female paratype UNS 00341/AMS R 173838." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4910730/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4910736>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Bayesian inference tree based on 16S ribosomal RNA mitochondrial gene sequences for species currently assigned to Gracixalus (Frost 2014) and for outgroups (Kurixalus eiffingeri, Kurixalus odontarsus, Philautus aurifasciatus, Polypedates leucomystax, and Rhacophorus reinwardtii). Numbers on branches are Bayesian posterior probabilities." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4910736/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

